            <h3>2. Archeveche Bridge (Paris)</h3>
            <p>The Archeveche Bridge is a bridge located near the Notre Dame Cathedral and
                was founded in 1828. What's unique about this bridge is, you can see hundreds of locked locks
                along the side of the bridge. These padlocks are from many couples who are at it
                in this place and make the padlock locked as a symbol and hope for a lasting relationship
                they. The lock key is then thrown into the river under the bridge.
                Well, this is done as a sign of the bond that their relationship remains as strong as a lock
                it remains tightly locked.      
            </p>
            
        </div>

    </div>
