            <h3>3. Notre Dame Cathedral (Paris)</h3>
            <p>Notre Dame Cathedral is the largest church in France with stylish architecture
                Gothic that is located on a small island called the Seine in the 12th century. Notre Dame Cathedral which means
                This “Our Mother in Paris” presents a beautiful and classic interior view.
                You can enjoy the beauty of the garden behind the Cathedral, you can see the view of the Seine from
                higher levels and dungeons that are open to the public.
            </p>
            
        </div>

    </div>
