        <div class="content">
            <h3>5. Arc de Triomphe (Paris)</h3>
            <p>The Arc de triomphe de l'Étoile or commonly known as the Arc de Triomphe is an arch-shaped monument
                victory in Paris which stands in the center of the Place de l'Étoile area, at the western end of the Champs-Élysées region. Building
                It was built on the orders of Napoleon Bonaparte with the aim of honoring the services of his great army.
                The Arc de Triomphe is not just a historical building of artistic value. The building has many statues depicting
                revolution and imperial era. There is also an eternal fire and a museum that stores various things related to the history of the building.
                The top of the building offers an amazing view of Paris.
                </p>
            
